Installation:

	git clone git://github.com/rjr89/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

	ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
	ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

	cd ~/.vim

1) This works without YCM
	git submodule init
	git submodule update

2) Here variant that should work with YouCompleteMe (not tested yet, and it works for Ubuntu, see YCM git repository):
	git submodule update --init --recursive
	cd ~/.vim/bundle/YouCompleteMe
	./install.py --clang-completer


Requirements:
	-) vimtex needs the package "latexmk" for compilation
